statement:
Circle the \emph{one} correct answer below. A linear system of four
equations in three unknowns has

\texttt{~(a)always~a~unique~solution}\\\texttt{~(b)either~a~unique~solution~or~no~solutions}\\\texttt{~(c)either~a~unique~solution~or~an~infinite~number~of~solutions}\\\texttt{~(d)either~no~solutions~or~an~infinite~number~of~solutions}\\\texttt{~(e)either~no~solutions,~a~unique~solution,~or~an~infinite~number~of~solutions}
